Ok... this map was one that took me a little while and I had a little fun doing it. The concept is the Terrorists are the exterminators, and the CT's are the molez. This means the T's can stay in their nice warm spawn and try to get HS on the CTs when they come out of a hole, or they can go into the molez' home. There is a buyzone for each side, very wide open, and pretty fun when you have a ton of people. Nightvision is alnost a necessity. ALSO: IF TEXTURES ARE FLASHING ON THE ROCKS, JUST SHOOT THEM. THEY WILL STOP.

The terrorists start at the top entrance that leads to the Granin Design Bureau, and have to work their way down the warehouse stairs. The CTs start on the docks and need to work their way inside the warehouse.

All battle points are within the warehouse: two entrances for the CTs, one defence-able position for the T's.

I created this map in homage to Metal Gear Solid 3: Snake Eater and it's gloriousness! 

Has a 3d skybox and is made to look as realistic as possible. Please rate if you enjoy, and check out metalgearsource.net for my current Metal Gear project!

This is a beta, but only because it has not been live server tested. It features fully custom optimized visleafs, a few secrets, and a customized bot file for offline play!

The teams are 10 versus 10.

It has been pakrat-ed, so their should be no missing textures or models! Please advise if otherwise.

This is the forst map I've submitted to FPSB, but not the first I've made. I'm looking to get feedback on this map so I can learn some more about mapping and what to do/how to fix things. 

People can use this map on any server. This can be edited as long as you ask permisssion first and credit me!

This map was originally named "aim_map_usp"
That map is located at http://www.fpsbanana.com/maps/11402

I revamped the map completely with the following changes:
- Textures have been replaced with custom lego textures by boharox
- Two extra entities have been added, meaning instead of 12 on each side there's now 13 on each side, they are also organized and aligned to be next to each other rather than some in front, some in back, you know.
- The wall art is still there. I did not touch it and personally, I think it looks pretty cool with the grey lego texture, looks more realistic.

This map folder includes three sub folders. One is for your server, one is for your fast download server, one contains the vmf if you would like to edit the map. You do NOT need the fast download files unless you have a fast download maps server. I put it in this zipped file as a courtesy :)

Don't forget to assess the map after playing it on FPSBanana!
If you have requests for me to edit any maps lemme know, I do not take credit for anyones original map and will always include a link to the original version
in my read me files.
